            <Title>稀缺Scarcity</Title>
            <Text>Scarcity is a key concept in economics. The fact is, there is only a limited supply of goods available for purchase. This factor often comes into play when a highly favored company’s stock price rockets skyward on the first day of its initial public offering (IPO). Driving the price is the relatively small number of shares available for trading, also called the float. Brisk demand plus limited supply equal higher prices!
稀缺是经济学的一个关键概念。 事实上，只有有限的货物供应可供购买。 在首次公开发行（IPO）的第一天，一个备受青睐的公司的股票价格猛涨的时候，这个因素通常会起作用。 推动价格是相对较少的可用于交易的股票，也被称为浮动。 轻快的需求加上有限的供应等于更高的价格！</Text>
