            <Title>备用系统Backup systems</Title>
            <Text>In engineering, backup systems are put into place to ensure the continuous functioning of critical infrastructure. This redundancy maintains the integrity of the system even if part of it fails. The same thought process applies to focus investing as well.
Image
When examining companies, you must make a series of decisions with an eye toward making an investment.
Image

When examining companies, you must make a series of decisions with an eye toward making an investment. You need to evaluate the economic health of the business—what the company will produce in future cash flows, for example, along with strength of management. The margin-of-safety principle is the focus investor’s backup system. Margin of safety holds that an investment should be made only when the price of the stock in question reflects a worst-case scenario, so that even if the investor’s projections are wrong, he or she won’t experience a dramatic loss in capital.</Text>
