            <Title>理性人Utility and rationality</Title>
            <Text>Economists assume that people will almost always try to maximize their happiness. In other words, people will try to obtain goods and services that provide the greatest utility or benefit. As we have discussed earlier, most economists also assume that people behave and choose rationally. While people do make sensible decisions a majority of the time, they become markedly less disciplined when they are stressed or have an incomplete understanding of a situation they are facing. These are the moments focus investors call opportunities!

While people do make sensible decisions a majority of the time, they become markedly less disciplined when they are stressed or have an incomplete understanding of a situation they are facing. These are the moments focus investors call opportunities!
经济学家们认为，人们几乎总是会尽量使自己的幸福感最大化。 换句话说，人们会试图获得最大效用或效益的商品和服务。 正如我们前面所讨论的，大多数经济学家也假定人们理性地行事和选择。 虽然大多数人确实做出了明智的决定，但是当他们受到压力或者对他们所面临的情况有不完全的理解时，他们显然没有被严格的纪律处分。 这些是投资者关注机会的时刻！

