            <Title>自然选择Natural selection</Title>
            <Text>Darwin developed the theory of natural selection by carefully observing wildlife during his travels aboard the HMS Beagle. While visiting the Galapagos Islands in 1835, he observed that each island supported its own variety of tortoise, mockingbird and finch. He further observed that the various individual species, though closely related, differed in structure and eating habits from one island to the next. These observations caused Darwin to ask if there were, in fact, possible links between the similar species.
After discussing with other scientists why and how the species on the islands were so similar, he developed a theory that evolution produces variations over time that favor some species (and certain varieties within species) over others. These variations and their resulting benefits are passed on to succeeding generations, thus increasing the likelihood of survival.
Natural selection is the most important biological concept for the focus investor to understand. Robert Hagstrom, in his book Latticework: The New Investing, explains it well when he writes, “Whereas in nature the process of evolution is one of natural selection, seeing the market with an evolutionary framework allows us to observe the law of economic selection.”39
This law of economic selection is readily observable in the business world. For example, one firm may develop a unique way of producing a product in a less expensive manner, which allows it to generate higher profits than other firms in the same line of business that are not employing this new process. As a result, the firm using the less expensive procedure should sell for a higher price/earnings (P/E) ratio than its competitors. The price (P) of the company stock divided by its earnings (E) is how this is calculated.

达尔文在HMS小猎犬旅行期间，通过仔细观察野生动物，发展了自然选择理论。他在1835年访问加拉帕戈斯群岛时，观察到每个岛屿都支持各种各样的乌龟，m鸟和雀科。他进一步观察到，不同种​​类的个体虽然密切相关，但在结构和饮食习惯上却各不相同。这些观察结果使得达尔文询问事实上是否有类似物种之间存在可能的联系。
在与其他科学家讨论为什么岛屿上的物种如此相似以后，他发展了一种理论，即随着时间的推移，进化会产生变化，有利于一些物种（以及某些品种）。这些变化及其带来的好处被传递给后代，从而增加了生存的可能性。
自然选择是重点投资者理解的最重要的生物学概念。罗伯特·哈格斯特罗姆（Robert Hagstrom）在其着作“新格局：新投资”一书中解释说：“在自然界，进化的过程是自然选择的过程之一，以进化框架看市场使我们能够观察经济选择的规律。 “39
经济选择的这一规律在商业世界中是很容易观察到的。例如，一家公司可能以较便宜的方式开发出一种独特的生产产品的方式，从而比同一行业中不采用这种新流程的其他公司获得更高的利润。因此，使用较便宜的程序的公司应该比竞争对手销售更高的市盈率（P / E）。公司股票的价格（P）除以盈利（E）是如何计算的。</Text>
